<br>
It is well known that when spells are freshly scribed that they are not the most efficient to cast.   In time, they become easier and will drain less of your resources.  (Not sure on the details, but there is an extra mana cost for spells until they are a level or two old.  So your 34 spells will cost you less, and your mana pool will be larger in a few levels).<br>
<br>
Do you know the cannidance?  This is a way that many shaman have managed to squeeze a little extra mana.<br>
<br>
(make a hotkey and label it canni. <br>
<br>
/sit off (in case you hit it when your sitting)<br>
/cast 8 (if canni is in your bottom spell slot)<br>
/pause 25 (have to mess around with this depending on your connection)<br>
/sit on.<br>
<br>
Now every six seconds the server updates your hitpoints based on regeneration, and naturak regen.  try to watch your hp or mana bar and when you see it update hit the button.  the effect is you catch the meditation tick, stand up canni, then sit down in time for the next med tick.  A very good way to cut downtime.  I generally aimed to keep my hp and mana bars about equal.  Also if there is downtime  and you are below half mana, let melee's bandage you to speed your mana regen).<br>
<br>
Now many folk want shaman spirits, fact is we can improve near everything on a fighter.   This becomes hard to do if you get into a fighter heavy group and have the additional duties of healing to go along with your normal debuffing and buffing.  The following is wise to consoder in these cases...<br>
<br>
1) In a fighter heavy group, leave the fighting to your pup and the fighters.  Fact is after 20's or so we fall way off the curve in melee effectiveness and your better spending yoru time doin the dance between heals and the like.<br>
<br>
Prioritize buffs. <br>
<br>
2) It will be very hard to keep regen on more than yourself and one other before the group version at 56 seasons.  its great to downtime heal, but only you, and the puller or main tank need to have it on all the time.  <br>
<br>
3) Talisman is good to keep on those who may take damage. Again, a rogue may never take more than a few hits all night, they really dont need the extra hitpoints, but can benefit from str and dex instead. <br>
<br>
4) Shield, again, only yourself and those taking hits need it. <br>
<br>
5) Stamina, yourself, and those taking hits.<br>
<br>
6) agi a bit of extra ac, so again on those who take hits. <br>
<br>
7) your dog wont be tanking for you for a long time.  He gets haste, and doesn't nee dmuch more.<br>
<br>
Finally, you decide who gets what buffs.  don't feel obligated to give every melee every buff, and feel free to say no.  If you are healer the buffs will have to be less than if you are just debuffing.<br>
<br>
Well, there's plenty more, but hopefully soemthing here will help. <br>
